column1: Timing results use CPU time and are averaged over 3 repeated tests.
compression ratios (uncompressed/compressed) by file and method
average is average of each compression ratio
total is sum of all corpus bytes / size of compressed corpus.
space saving ratios (1 - compressed/uncompressed) by file and method
average is average of each compression ratio
total is sum of all corpus bytes / size of compressed corpus.
compression durations (s) by file and method
compression rates (Mb/s) by file and method
total is corpus size / time to compress corpus. total will be more affected by larger files
average is average of each compression rate. compression rate doesn't look great for small files.
decompression durations (s) by file and method
decompression rates (decompressed Mb/s) by file and method
total is corpus size / time to decompress corpus. total will be more affected by larger files
average is average of each decompression rate. rate doesn't look great for small files.
1e6*(uncompressed bits - compressed bits) / (compression time + decompression time)
total is (corpus size - compressed corpus size) / time to compress and decompress corpus. total will be more affected by larger files
average is average of each rate. rate doesn't look great for small files.
